   * :attr:	:xmlattr:`ControlLockTimer`
     :val:	0...120
     :def:	20 sec
     :desc:	Control command lock timer is used to poll only one outstation for a configured number of seconds after sending a control command.
		All other outstations that share the same hardware channel (e.g. serial port) are temporary excluded from polling while :include-arg:`1` operates.
		This feature enables to speed up reception of a control command feedback. 
		:include-arg:`1` can only be used if more than one outstation share the hardware channel.
		Value 0 disables control lock timer feature.
